---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About" description="Built by Biswajit Jana — the science and technology behind this platform">

  <section style="padding:7rem 1.5rem 4rem;max-width:780px;margin:0 auto;">

    <!-- Eyebrow -->
    <div style="
      display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;
      background:rgba(96,165,250,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25);
      border-radius:50px;padding:0.35rem 1rem;
      font-size:0.75rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.1em;text-transform:uppercase;
      color:#93c5fd;margin-bottom:1.5rem;
    ">🔭 About this Platform</div>

    <h1 style="
      font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;
      font-size:clamp(2.2rem,5vw,3.5rem);
      font-weight:900;margin-bottom:2rem;
      background:linear-gradient(135deg,#93c5fd,#a78bfa,#f0abfc);
      -webkit-background-clip:text;-webkit-text-fill-color:transparent;background-clip:text;
    ">Where Astrophysics Meets the Web</h1>

    <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:2rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.72);font-size:0.97rem;line-height:1.75;">

      <div class="card">
        <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.25rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          🎓 The Science Behind It
        </h2>
        <p>
          This platform is built by an astrophysics researcher — studying
          stellar evolution, exoplanet detection via transit photometry and radial velocity, and
          computational simulations of gravitational dynamics. Every number, every unit, and every
          habitability metric is grounded in peer-reviewed methods.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.25rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          🛠 Technology Stack
        </h2>
        <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:0.5rem;font-size:0.85rem;">
          {[
            ['Astro 4.x', 'Static site generation + islands'],
            ['React 18', 'Interactive UI components'],
            ['Three.js / R3F', '3D WebGL solar system'],
            ['@react-three/drei', 'OrbitControls, Stars, Html'],
            ['Tailwind CSS', 'Utility-first styling'],
            ['NASA Exoplanet API', 'Live planetary data'],
            ['NASA APOD API', 'Daily astronomy images'],
            ['Vercel', 'Global CDN deployment'],
          ].map(([tech, desc]) => (
            <div style={{
              background:'rgba(255,255,255,0.04)',
              border:'1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.07)',
              borderRadius:10,padding:'0.6rem 0.85rem',
            }}>
              <div style={{fontWeight:700,color:'#a78bfa',fontSize:'0.82rem',marginBottom:'0.15rem'}}>{tech}</div>
              <div style={{color:'rgba(255,255,255,0.45)',fontSize:'0.75rem'}}>{desc}</div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.25rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          📡 Data Sources
        </h2>
        <ul style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;padding-left:0;list-style:none;">
          {[
            ['NASA Exoplanet Archive', 'https://exoplanetarchive.ipac.caltech.edu', '5,700+ confirmed exoplanets'],
            ['NASA APOD API', 'https://api.nasa.gov', 'Daily astronomy image'],
            ['IAU Minor Planet Center', 'https://www.minorplanetcenter.net', 'Asteroid data'],
            ['Open Exoplanet Catalogue', 'https://github.com/openexoplanetcatalogue', 'Supplemental data'],
          ].map(([name, url, note]) => (
            <li style={{
              display:'flex',alignItems:'center',gap:'0.75rem',
              padding:'0.6rem 0',
              borderBottom:'1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)',
            }}>
              <span style={{width:8,height:8,borderRadius:'50%',background:'#a78bfa',flexShrink:0}} />
              <div>
                <a href={url} target="_blank" rel="noopener" style={{
                  color:'#93c5fd',fontWeight:600,fontSize:'0.88rem',textDecoration:'none',
                }}>{name}</a>
                <div style={{color:'rgba(255,255,255,0.4)',fontSize:'0.76rem'}}>{note}</div>
              </div>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif;font-weight:800;font-size:1.25rem;color:#fff;margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          ⚙️ Habitability Index
        </h2>
        <p style="margin-bottom:0.75rem;">
          The habitability score shown on each exoplanet card is a simplified proxy for the
          <strong style="color:#c4b5fd;">Earth Similarity Index (ESI)</strong>. It weighs:
        </p>
        <ul style="list-style:none;padding:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.4rem;font-size:0.88rem;">
          <li>🔵 <strong>Radius (60%)</strong> — planets near Earth's size (0.7–1.5 R⊕) score highest</li>
          <li>🟡 <strong>Orbital period (40%)</strong> — periods 200–600 days suggest habitable-zone positioning</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.82rem;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.45);">
          Note: True habitability requires stellar luminosity, eccentricity, atmospheric data, and more.
          This is a first-order approximation from available catalog data.
        </p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
